      "*": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b><a href=\"/Main_Page\" title=\"Main Page\">Home</a> * <a href=\"/People\" title=\"People\">People</a> * Reinhard Scharnagl</b>\n</p>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:252px;\"><a href=\"https://plus.google.com/u/0/108847251854374603679/posts\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/4/43/ReinhardScharnagl.jpg\" width=\"250\" height=\"250\" class=\"thumbimage\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/File:ReinhardScharnagl.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Reinhard Scharnagl <sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></div></div></div> \n<p><b>Reinhard Scharnagl</b>, (died in August 2015)<br />\nwas a German computer chess programmer, and author of the chess program <a href=\"/SMIRF\" title=\"SMIRF\">SMIRF</a>. \nReinhard was pioneer in <a href=\"/Chess960\" title=\"Chess960\">Fischer Random Chess</a> (FRC / Chess960) <sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> as well for chess variants with other board sizes like 10x8. \nOn August 01, 2015 he posted on his Google+ site that he survived three weeks of <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chemotherapy\">chemotherapy</a> and <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Radiation_therapy\">radiation therapy</a> fighting <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Brain_tumor\">brain tumor</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>. \nHe died soon later that month in August 2015 <sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> <sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>. \n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Publications\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Publications</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Forum_Posts\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Forum Posts</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#2000_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2000 ...</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#2005_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2005 ...</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#2010_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2010 ...</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#2015\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2015</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#External_Links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External Links</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-8\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Publications\">Publications</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Reinhard_Scharnagl&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Publications\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<ul><li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Reinhard Scharnagl</a> (<b>2004</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books/about/Fischer_Random_Schach.html?id=DEatvtAx9RQC&amp;redir_esc=y\">Fischer-Random-Schach: (FRC/Chess 960)</a></i>. Books on Demand (German) <sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Reinhard Scharnagl</a> (<b>2014</b>). <i>Chess960 / FRC: Des Schachspiels revolutionäre Zukunft</i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.amazon.de/Chess960-FRC-Schachspiels-revolution%C3%A4re-Zukunft-ebook/dp/B00L15GNO0\">Amazon.de: Kindle Edition</a> (German)</li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Forum_Posts\">Forum Posts</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Reinhard_Scharnagl&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Forum Posts\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"2000_...\">2000 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Reinhard_Scharnagl&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: 2000 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=334328\">Re: ASCII Board representation</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Reinhard Scharnagl</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, December 08, 2003</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=403318\">Re:On SMIRF</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Reinhard Scharnagl</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, December 30, 2004</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"2005_...\">2005 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Reinhard_Scharnagl&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: 2005 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=437213\">Why to use compatible X-FEN (in Chess960)</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Reinhard Scharnagl</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, July 17, 2005&#160;» <a href=\"/Forsyth-Edwards_Notation#X-FEN\" title=\"Forsyth-Edwards Notation\">X-FEN</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=437253\">for Reinhard Scharnagl about Chess960</a> by <a href=\"/Matthias_Gemuh\" title=\"Matthias Gemuh\">Matthias Gemuh</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, July 18, 2005</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.open-aurec.com/wbforum/viewtopic.php?f=4&amp;t=3141\">Best BitBoard LSB funktion?</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Reinhard Scharnagl</a>, <a href=\"/Computer_Chess_Forums\" title=\"Computer Chess Forums\">Winboard Forum</a>, July 20, 2005&#160;» <a href=\"/BitScan\" title=\"BitScan\">BitScan</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=439792\">Chess960: X-FEN rules international</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Reinhard Scharnagl</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, August 03, 2005</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://rybkaforum.net/cgi-bin/rybkaforum/topic_show.pl?tid=2191\">Scharnagl from Munich, Germany</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Octopus</a>, <a href=\"/Computer_Chess_Forums\" title=\"Computer Chess Forums\">Rybka Forum</a>, September 18, 2007</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=21403\">Search extensions at promising trajectories</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Reinhard Scharnagl</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, May 28, 2008&#160;» <a href=\"/Extensions\" title=\"Extensions\">Extensions</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"2010_...\">2010 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Reinhard_Scharnagl&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: 2010 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.open-chess.org/viewtopic.php?f=39&amp;t=1039\">Computerschach mit monochromen Methoden&#160;?</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Reinhard Scharnagl</a>, <a href=\"/Computer_Chess_Forums\" title=\"Computer Chess Forums\">OpenChess - Deutsches Forum</a>, January 27, 2011 (German)</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.open-aurec.com/wbforum/viewtopic.php?f=4&amp;t=52093\">Starting to use the Winboard Protocol</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Reinhard Scharnagl</a>, <a href=\"/Computer_Chess_Forums\" title=\"Computer Chess Forums\">Winboard Forum</a>, December 11, 2011</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=42111\">SMIRF engine project terminated</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Reinhard Scharnagl</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, January 22, 2012</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.open-chess.org/viewtopic.php?f=7&amp;t=1906\">Smirf 8x8/10x8 on USB Stick</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Octopus</a>, <a href=\"/Computer_Chess_Forums\" title=\"Computer Chess Forums\">OpenChess Forum</a>, March 16, 2012</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=53864\">Little progress on SMIRF's successor program</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Reinhard Scharnagl</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, September 28, 2014</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"2015\">2015</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Reinhard_Scharnagl&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" title=\"Edit section: 2015\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=55274\">Some Chess960/FRC positions to be confirmed</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Reinhard Scharnagl</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, February 09, 2015&#160;» <a href=\"/Chess960\" title=\"Chess960\">Chess960</a>, <a href=\"/Perft_Results\" title=\"Perft Results\">Perft Results</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=55424\">Detail evaluation within quiescence search</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Reinhard Scharnagl</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, February 22, 2015</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=55427\">hanging piece at starting quiescence search - how to handle?</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Reinhard Scharnagl</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, February 22, 2015&#160;» <a href=\"/Hanging_Piece\" title=\"Hanging Piece\">Hanging Piece</a>, <a href=\"/Quiescence_Search\" title=\"Quiescence Search\">Quiescence Search</a></li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_Links\">External Links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Reinhard_Scharnagl&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" title=\"Edit section: External Links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.chessvariants.com/contests/10/crc.html\">Capablanca Random Chess - Proposal</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.fotocommunity.de/fotograf/reinhard-scharnagl/1411112\">Reinhard Scharnagl - Fotos &amp; Bilder - Fotograf aus Büttelborn Klein-Gerau, Deutschland | fotocommunity</a></li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket